      "content": "that makes sense for the debate. can u expand on the \"family values\" and \"social norms\" thing? like, if i'm trying to make a sophisticated argument, how would someone use that to say that integration is actually bad for the sociological health of a community? basically, what would be the \"pro-segregation\" stance on how different cultures or racial groups affect the stability of the traditional family unit or societal norms?",
